 THE Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has advised the electorate in Ondo State to vet the list and particulars of nominated candidates for the October 10 governorship election. It said this is necessary to enhance transparency in the party nomination processes. INEC in a statement signed by the National Commissioner and Chairman Information and Voter Education Committee, Festus Okoye, said 17 of the 18 registered parties gave the commission the requisite statutory notice of their intention to conduct primaries and “they conducted primaries for the purposes of nominating candidates for the Governorship Election.” The statement said: “On February 6, the commission published the Timetable and Schedule of Activities for the Ondo Governorship Election and gave parties interested in sponsoring and nominating candidates between July 2 and 25 to conduct primaries and till 6pm on July 28 for the submission of the list and particulars of nominated candidates. “Seventeen of the 18 registered parties gave the commission the requisite statutory notice of their intention to conduct primaries and they conducted primaries to nominate candidates for the Governorship Election.” It added: “The commission opened its dedicated nomination portal on July 21 and some of the parties that conducted their primaries before the July 25 deadline took the opportunity and uploaded the list and particulars of their nominated candidates ahead of the cut off time of 6pm on July 28. As at 4.08pm today (July 28) 17 parties had submitted the list and particulars of their nominated candidates, using the INEC dedicated portal. “The list and particulars of the candidates as submitted by the 17 parties will be uploaded on our website and published at our state office in Akure on July 31. This is in compliance with Section 31(3) of the Electoral Act 2010 (as amended). The list will also be published on the commission’s social media platforms on the same day.” 